OL,3,CRoofer jailed for leaving widow almost
OL,4,C#13,000 out of pocket
OL,6,FA Salford roofer has been jailed after
OL,7,Fleaving an elderly widow with a badly
OL,8,Fdamaged roof almost #13,000 out of
OL,9,Fpocket.
OL,11,FPreston Crown Court heard that
OL,12,FChristopher Parr, 37, trading as Up
OL,13,Fand Over Roofing and Building, was
OL,14,Foriginally called out to look at a
OL,15,Fleaking skylight.
OL,17,FBut he quickly told his unsuspecting
OL,18,Fvictim that additional work was
OL,19,Fneeded, to which she agreed.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
