OL,3,CRoofer jailed for leaving widow almost
OL,4,C#13,000 out of pocket
OL,6,FWhile the work was being undertaken,
OL,7,Fhe removed roof tiles from a large
OL,8,Fsection of the roof before telling the
OL,9,Fwoman that this part of the roof
OL,10,Fneeded to be replaced.
OL,12,FGiven that an area of tiles had
OL,13,Falready been removed, she felt she had
OL,14,Fno alternative but to agree to the
OL,15,Fwork and made five payments into
OL,16,FParr's bank account totalling #7,800.
OL,18,FHe then failed to return to complete
OL,19,Fthe work, giving a string of excuses
OL,20,Fover three to four months as to why he
OL,21,Fcouldn't finish it off.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
