OL,3,CRoofer jailed for leaving widow almost
OL,4,C#13,000 out of pocket
OL,6,FShe then had to pay another trader to
OL,7,Freinstall the roof, at a cost of
OL,8,F#4,777, and pay a further #300 for
OL,9,Fredecoration of a room due to a leak
OL,10,Fin the roof when it was left exposed
OL,11,Fto the elements by Parr.
OL,13,FAn independent report commissioned by
OL,14,FSalford Council's Trading Standards
OL,15,Fteam found substandard work had been
OL,16,Fcarried out with zero value, and that
OL,17,Fthe victim would incur additional
OL,18,Fcosts in rectifying the work.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
