OL,3,CRoofer jailed for leaving widow almost
OL,4,C#13,000 out of pocket
OL,6,FMeanwhile the roofer was also being
OL,7,Finvestigated by Lancashire Trading
OL,8,FStandards officers, eventually landing
OL,9,Fin Preston Crown Court for both cases.
OL,11,FParr, of Filey Drive in Salford, was
OL,12,Fsentenced to 27 months in prison and
OL,13,Fordered to pay full compensation of
OL,14,F#12,887 to his victim at Preston Crown
OL,15,FCourt.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
